ria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 12, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eef1665703174430.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eef1665703174430.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eef1665703174430.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eef1665703174430\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Authenticate the user name and password combination.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eef1665703174430__section_w2065ab1b5b1_w2066ab1b5_w2067ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d683463e49\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Client/server security drivers</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eef1665703174430__section_w2068ab1b5b3_w2069ab1b5_w2070ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d683463e58\">Return Values</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"eef1665703174430__parml_zc1_zqp_dwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">USEC_SUCCESS</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Authentication successful, no information returned</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">USEC_ERROR</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Authentication failed, error returned in Error members </dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eef1665703174430__section_w2071ab1b5b5_w2072ab1b5_w2073ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d683463e85\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eef1665703174430__p_d132026e1_d132027e1_d132028e1\">Authenticate the user name and password combination.\n        The user name and passwords are null-terminated strings provided in the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Username</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">Passwd</code> members of the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">uSecDrv</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eef1665703174430__p_d132029e1_d132030e1_d132031e1\">On Microsoft Windows platforms, a user token is\n        required to create a process running under that user account. Irrespective of the validation\n        scheme used, a successful validation must deliver a user token (in\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">UserToken</code>), suitable for use in the Windows function\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">CreateProcessAsUser()</code>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527097\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527097\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "USEC_AUTHENTICATE Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 12, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Authenticate the user name and password combination. Use Client/server security drivers Return Values USEC_SUCCESS Authentication successful, no information returned USEC_ERROR Authentication failed, error returned in Error members Description Authenticate the user name and password combination. The user name and passwords are null-terminated strings provided in the Username and Passwd members of the uSecDrv . On Microsoft Windows platforms, a user token is required to create a process running under that user account. Irrespective of the validation scheme used, a successful validation must deliver a user token (in UserToken ), suitable for use in the Windows function CreateProcessAsUser() . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}